<section id="problem" class="container-full section-space">
  <div class="grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,0.85fr)_minmax(0,1.15fr)] lg:gap-16">
    <div class="max-w-xl min-w-0">
      <p class="label-accent">The problem</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 text-section-title text-balance">
        AI activity is not the same as business value.
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-[700px] min-w-0">
      <p class="text-lg leading-[1.7] text-ink">
        Licence usage, prompts submitted and employees trained are activity measures. They do not show
        whether AI has reduced cost, released usable capacity, improved conversion, increased gross
        profit or lowered operational risk.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-6 text-[0.9375rem] leading-[1.7] text-muted md:text-base">
        The useful question is not whether people are using AI. It is whether each initiative should
        be stopped, repaired, consolidated or expanded, and what evidence supports that decision.
      </p>

      <aside class="quote-mark mt-8 border-l-2 border-transparent pl-6" data-reveal style="--i: 0">
        <p class="font-display text-xl font-semibold leading-[1.45] text-ink md:text-2xl">
          Time saved has no financial value until the business can use it.
        </p>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
